          <physDesc>
            <p>Paper, about 6 5/8 in. by 5, consisting of 126 leaves, some of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 1—3, 13, 30, 118, 124 and 125. The quires, signed with letters, seem to have been 16 in number. Leaves are wanting at the beginning, as well as after foll. 1, 4, 23, 30, 40, 46, 123, and 125. There are from 16 to 19 lines in each page. </p>
